<_X_chapter sid="1KI 4">
<verse sid="1KI 4:1"/>And King Salomon was ruling over Israel,<verse eid="1KI 4:1"/>

<verse sid="1KI 4:2"/>and these were the rulers who were his: Azariou son of Sadok<verse eid="1KI 4:2"/>

<verse sid="1KI 4:3"/>and Eliareph and Achia son of Saba, secretaries, and Iosaphat son of Achilid, recorder,<verse eid="1KI 4:3"/>

<verse sid="1KI 4:4"/>and Sadouch and Abiathar, priests,<verse eid="1KI 4:4"/>

<verse sid="1KI 4:5"/>and Ornia son of Nathan, over the officials, and Zabouth son of Nathan, the king's companion,<verse eid="1KI 4:5"/>

<verse sid="1KI 4:6"/>and Achiel, steward, and Eliab son of Saph, over the paternal family, and Adoniram son of Ephra, over the levy.<verse eid="1KI 4:6"/>

<verse sid="1KI 4:7"/>And Salomon had twelve appointed over all Israel to provide for the king and his household; it would be that for one month in the year the one would provide.<verse eid="1KI 4:7"/>

<verse sid="1KI 4:8"/>And these are their names: Benor in the hill country of Ephraim, one;<verse eid="1KI 4:8"/>

<verse sid="1KI 4:9"/>son of Rechab in Mackemas and Bethalamin and Baithsamus and Ailon as far as Baithanan, one;<verse eid="1KI 4:9"/>

<verse sid="1KI 4:10"/>son of Esoth Berbethnema, Lousamencha and Resphara;<verse eid="1KI 4:10"/>

<verse sid="1KI 4:11"/>Chinanadab and Anaphathi, a man of Tableth (his wife was a daughter of Salomon) , one;<verse eid="1KI 4:11"/>

<verse sid="1KI 4:12"/>Bakcha son of Achilid Thaanach and Mekedo and all the house of San which is beside Sesathan below the Esrae and from Baisaphoud Ebelmaola as far as Maeber Loukam, one;<verse eid="1KI 4:12"/>

<verse sid="1KI 4:13"/>son of Gaber in Remath Galaad, and to this the allotment Eregaba, which is in Basan, sixty great cities with walls and bronze bars, one;<verse eid="1KI 4:13"/>

<verse sid="1KI 4:14"/>Achinadab son of Achel Maanain, one;<verse eid="1KI 4:14"/>

<verse sid="1KI 4:15"/>Achimaas, in Nephthali (and he took Basemmath, Salomon's daughter, as wife) , one;<verse eid="1KI 4:15"/>

<verse sid="1KI 4:16"/>Baana son of Chousi in Maalath, one;<verse eid="1KI 4:16"/>

<verse sid="1KI 4:17"/>Samaa son of Ela in Beniamin;<verse eid="1KI 4:17"/>

<verse sid="1KI 4:18"/>Gaber son of Adai in the land of Gad, the land of King Seon of Hesebon and of King Og of Basan; and one nasiph<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">4:18</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'official'</char></note> in the land of Ioudas;<verse eid="1KI 4:18"/>

<verse sid="1KI 4:19"/>Iosaphat son of Phouasoud in Issachar.<verse eid="1KI 4:19"/>
</_X_chapter>




