<verse sid="1KI 5:1"/>(4.27) And thus the officials would supply provisions for King Salomon and everything ordered for the table of the king, each one in his month, they did not alter a thing, and they also used to bring to the place where the king might be barley and straw for the horses and the chariots, each according to his charge.<verse eid="1KI 5:1"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:2"/>(4.22) And these were Salomon's provisions for one day: thirty kors<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">5:2</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew 1 kor = 220 liters</char></note> of choice flour and sixty korsb of ground meal<verse eid="1KI 5:2"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:3"/>(4.23) and ten choice calves and twenty pasture-fed oxen and one hundred sheep, besides deer and gazelles and choice birds, grain fed<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">5:3</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'grain fed':  I.e. 'the sheep'</char></note>.<verse eid="1KI 5:3"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:4"/>(4.24) For he was ruler across the river, and he was at peace on all sides round about.<verse eid="1KI 5:4"/>

