<verse sid="1KI 5:9"/>(4.29) And the Lord gave Salomon discernment and very great wisdom and volume of mind like the sand that is by the sea,<verse eid="1KI 5:9"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:10"/>(4.30) and Salomon was greatly multiplied, above the discernment of all ancient people and above all the discerning of Egypt.<verse eid="1KI 5:10"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:11"/>(4.31) And he was wise beyond all humans; he was wise beyond Gaithan the Ezraite and Haiman and Chalkal and Darda, sons of Mal.<verse eid="1KI 5:11"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:12"/>(4.32) And Salomon spoke three thousand illustrations, and his songs were five thousand.<verse eid="1KI 5:12"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:13"/>(4.33) And he spoke of trees, from the cedar that is in Lebanon and as far as the hyssop that comes out through the wall, and he spoke of animals and of birds and of reptiles and of fish.<verse eid="1KI 5:13"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:14"/>(4.34) And all the people used to come to hear the wisdom of Salomon, and he would receive gifts from all the kings of the earth who were hearing of his wisdom. <para style="p"/><verse eid="1KI 5:14"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:14a"/>(14a) (3.1) And Salomon took the daughter of Pharao for himself for a wife and brought her into the city of Dauid until he finished the house of the Lord and his own house and the wall of Ierousalem.<verse eid="1KI 5:14a"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:14b"/>(14b) Then Pharao king of Egypt went up and captured Gazer and burned it and the Canaan-ite who lived in Mergab, and Pharao gave them<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">5:14</char><char closed="false" style="ft">I.e. 'Gazer' and 'Mergab'</char></note> as send-off to his daughter, Salomon's wife, and Salomon built Gazer.<verse eid="1KI 5:14b"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:15"/>(5.1) And King Chiram of Tyre sent his servants to anoint Salomon in place of his father Dauid, for Chiram had affection for Dauid all the days.<verse eid="1KI 5:15"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:16"/>(5.2) And Salomon sent to Chiram, saying,<verse eid="1KI 5:16"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:17"/>(5.3) "You know my father Dauid that he could not build a house for the name of the Lord, my God, from the presence of the wars that surrounded him until the Lord put them under the traces of his feet.<verse eid="1KI 5:17"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:18"/>(5.4) And now the Lord my God gave me rest all around; there is no plotter, and there is no evil encounter.<verse eid="1KI 5:18"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:19"/>(5.5) And behold, I intend to build a house for the name of the Lord, my God, as the Lord God spoke to my father Dauid, saying, 'Your son whom I will give on your throne in your place, this one shall build the house for my name.'<verse eid="1KI 5:19"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:20"/>(5.6) And now command, and let them cut timber from Lebanon for me, and behold, my slaves are with your slaves, and I will give you the wages of your services according to all that you say, for you know that we have no one who knows how to cut timber like the Sidonians."<verse eid="1KI 5:20"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:21"/>(5.7) And it happened, when Chiram heard the words of Salomon, he rejoiced greatly and said, "Blessed be God today, who gave to Dauid a discerning son over this numerous people."<verse eid="1KI 5:21"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:22"/>(5.8) And he sent to Salomon, saying, "I have heard concerning all that you sent to me; I will do your every wish, cedar timber and pine.<verse eid="1KI 5:22"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:23"/>(5.9) My slaves shall bring them down to the sea from Lebanon, and I will make them rafts to the place that you indicate to me, and I will have them broken up there, and you will take them away, and you shall do my wish by providing food for my household."<verse eid="1KI 5:23"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:24"/>(5.10) And Chiram was giving Salomon cedars and his every wish.<verse eid="1KI 5:24"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:25"/>(5.11) And Salomon in turn gave Chiram twenty thousand kors<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">5:25</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew 1 kor = 220 liters</char></note> of wheat and machir<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">5:25</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'price'</char></note> for his household and twenty thousand beth<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">5:25</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew 1 bath = 22 liters</char></note> of beaten oil; like this Salomon would give to Chiram yearly.<verse eid="1KI 5:25"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:26"/>(5.12) And the Lord gave Salomon wisdom, as he spoke to him, and there was peace between Chiram and between Salomon, and they made a covenant between themselves.<verse eid="1KI 5:26"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:27"/>(5.13) And the king raised a levy out of all Israel, and the levy was thirty thousand men.<verse eid="1KI 5:27"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:28"/>(5.14) And he sent them to Lebanon, ten thousand a month alternating, they were a month in Lebanon and two months in their home, and Adoniram was in charge of the levy.<verse eid="1KI 5:28"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:29"/>(5.15) And Salomon had seventy thousand bearing a burden and eighty thousand stonecutters in the hill country,<verse eid="1KI 5:29"/>

<verse sid="1KI 5:30"/>(5.16) besides the rulers appointed over Salomon's works, three thousand six hundred supervisors who managed the works.<verse eid="1KI 5:30"/>

