<_X_chapter sid="1KI 6">
<verse sid="1KI 6:1"/>And it happened, in the four hundred fortieth year of the departure of the sons of Israel from Egypt, in the fourth year in the second month, when King Salomon reigned over Israel, <para style="p"/><verse eid="1KI 6:1"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:1a"/>(1a) that the king commanded, and they took great, costly stones for the foundation of the house, and unhewn stones,<verse eid="1KI 6:1a"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:1b"/>(1b) and the sons of Salomon and the sons of Chiram hewed and laid them.<verse eid="1KI 6:1b"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:1c"/>(1c) In the fourth year he laid the foundation of the house of the Lord in the month Niso, the second month;<verse eid="1KI 6:1c"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:1d"/>(1d) in the eleventh year in the month Baal (this is the eighth month) the house was finished in all its plan and in all its arrangement.<verse eid="1KI 6:1d"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:2"/>And the house that King Salomon built for the Lord, forty cubits its length and twenty its width in cubits and twenty-five its height in cubits.<verse eid="1KI 6:2"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:3"/>And the ailam<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">6:3</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'porch'</char></note> in front of the shrine, twenty its width in cubits for the width of the house and ten its depth in cubits in front of the house. (6.14) And he built the house and finished it.<verse eid="1KI 6:3"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:4"/>And for the house he made hidden, peep windows.<verse eid="1KI 6:4"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:5"/>And he placed beams on the wall of the house all around the shrine and the dabir<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">6:5</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'inner chamber'</char></note>, and he made sides all around.<verse eid="1KI 6:5"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:6"/>The lower side five cubits its width and the middle six and the third<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">6:6</char><char closed="false" style="ft">I.e. 'side'</char></note> seven its width in cubits; he gave the house a space all around, outside the house, in order that they should not lay hold of the walls of the house.<verse eid="1KI 6:6"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:7"/>And the house while it was being built was built with rough, unworked stones, neither hammer nor ax nor any tool of iron was heard in the house while it was being built.<verse eid="1KI 6:7"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:8"/>And the gateway of the lower side was under the right shoulder<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">6:8</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Or 'angle'</char></note> of the house, and there was a winding ascent into the middle and from the middle to the third-story.<verse eid="1KI 6:8"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:9"/>And he built the house and finished it, and he made a coffered ceiling for the house from cedars.<verse eid="1KI 6:9"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:10"/>And he built the bondings through the whole house, its height five in cubits, and he enclosed the bonding with cedar boards.<verse eid="1KI 6:10"/>

<verse _X_reasonEmpty="verseEmptyInThisTranslation" sid="1KI 6:11"/><char style="no">&amp;#x2013;</char><note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">6:11</char><char closed="false" style="ft">This verse is empty in this translation.</char></note><verse eid="1KI 6:11"/>

<verse _X_reasonEmpty="verseEmptyInThisTranslation" sid="1KI 6:12"/>&amp;#x2013;<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">6:12</char><char closed="false" style="ft">This verse is empty in this translation.</char></note><verse eid="1KI 6:12"/>

<verse _X_reasonEmpty="verseEmptyInThisTranslation" sid="1KI 6:13"/><char style="no">&amp;#x2013;</char><note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">6:13</char><char closed="false" style="ft">This verse is empty in this translation.</char></note><verse eid="1KI 6:13"/>

<verse _X_reasonEmpty="verseEmptyInThisTranslation" sid="1KI 6:14"/>&amp;#x2013;<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">6:14</char><char closed="false" style="ft">This verse is empty in this translation.</char></note><verse eid="1KI 6:14"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:15"/>And he built the walls of the house with cedar boards from the floor of the house and as far as the rafters and to the walls; he made a coffered ceiling enclosed with boards within, and he covered the inside of the house with sides of pine.<verse eid="1KI 6:15"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:16"/>And he built the twenty cubits from the top of the house, the one side from the floor to the rafters, and he made from the dabir<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">6:16</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'inner chamber'</char></note> to the holy of holies.<verse eid="1KI 6:16"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:17"/>And the shrine was forty cubits in front of<verse eid="1KI 6:17"/>

<verse _X_reasonEmpty="verseEmptyInThisTranslation" sid="1KI 6:18"/><char style="no">&amp;#x2013;</char><note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">6:18</char><char closed="false" style="ft">This verse is empty in this translation.</char></note><verse eid="1KI 6:18"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:19"/>the dabir<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">6:19</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'inner chamber'</char></note> in the midst of the house within, to set there the ark of the covenant of the Lord.<verse eid="1KI 6:19"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:20"/>The length twenty cubits and twenty cubits the width and twenty cubits its height, and he covered it with overlaid gold. And he made an altar<verse eid="1KI 6:20"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:21"/>in front of the dabir<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">6:21</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'inner chamber'</char></note> and overlaid it with gold.<verse eid="1KI 6:21"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:22"/>And he overlaid the whole house with gold until the completion of all the house.<verse eid="1KI 6:22"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:23"/>And in the dabir<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">6:23</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'inner chamber'</char></note> he made two cheroubin of ten cubits measured size.<verse eid="1KI 6:23"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:24"/>And five cubits the wing of the one cheroub and five cubits its second wing and from the tip of its wing to the tip of its wing ten in cubits;<verse eid="1KI 6:24"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:25"/>thus it was with the second cheroub, with one measure one completion for both.<verse eid="1KI 6:25"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:26"/>And the height of the one cheroub ten in cubits and so the second cheroub.<verse eid="1KI 6:26"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:27"/>And both the cheroubin were in the midst of the innermost house and he spread out their wings, and one wing was touching the wall, and a wing of the second was touching the wall, and their other wings which were in the midst of the house were touching wing to wing.<verse eid="1KI 6:27"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:28"/>And he overlaid the cheroubin with gold.<verse eid="1KI 6:28"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:29"/>And with a stylus he inscribed all the walls of the house, round about, with engraved cheroubin, and the inner and the outer had palm trees.<verse eid="1KI 6:29"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:30"/>And the floor of the house he overlaid with gold, of the innermost and of the outermost.<verse eid="1KI 6:30"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:31"/>And for the doorway of the dabire he made doors of juniper wood and a five-sided lintel<verse eid="1KI 6:31"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:32"/>and two doors of pine boards and carved on them carved cheroubin and palm trees and open flower-leaves, and he overlaid with gold, and the gold went down on the cheroubin and on the palm trees.<verse eid="1KI 6:32"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:33"/>And thus he made for the gateway to the shrine lintels of juniper, four-sided porticoes.<verse eid="1KI 6:33"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:34"/>And pine boards in both the doors; the one door two leaves and their hinges and the second door two leaves, hinged;<verse eid="1KI 6:34"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:35"/>carved cheroubin and palm trees and open flowers-leaves and overlaid with gold brought down upon the relief work.<verse eid="1KI 6:35"/>

<verse sid="1KI 6:36"/>And he built the inner court, three courses of unhewn stones and a course of prepared cedar round about. And he built the veil of the court of the ailam of the house, which is before the shrine.<verse eid="1KI 6:36"/>
</_X_chapter>




