<_X_chapter sid="1KI 7">
<verse sid="1KI 7:1"/>(13) And King Salomon sent and received Chiram from Tyre,<verse eid="1KI 7:1"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:2"/>(14) son of a widow, and he was from the tribe of Nephthali, and his father was a Tyrian man, an artisan in bronze and accomplished in skill and understanding and knowledge to perform every work in bronze, and he was brought in to King Salomon, and he made all the works.<verse eid="1KI 7:2"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:3"/>(15) And he cast the two pillars for the ailam of the house; eighteen cubits was the height of a pillar, and a circumference of fourteen cubits encompassed it, and the thickness of the pillar was the hollow of four fingers, and so the second pillar.<verse eid="1KI 7:3"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:4"/>(16) And he made two covers of molten bronze to set on the tops of the pillars, five cubits the height of the one cover and five cubits the height of the second cover.<verse eid="1KI 7:4"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:5"/>(17) And he made two lattice works to wrap around the cover of the pillars, and a lattice-work for the one cover and a lattice work for the second cover<verse eid="1KI 7:5"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:6"/>(18) and a hanging work, two rows of bronze pomegranates wrought in net-works, a hanging work, row upon row, and thus he did with the second cover.<verse eid="1KI 7:6"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:7"/>(21) And he set up the pillars of the ailam of the shrine, and he set up the one pillar and called its name Iachoum, and he set up the second pillar and called its name Baaz.<verse eid="1KI 7:7"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:8"/>(19) And on the tops of the pillars was lily-work of four cubits, against the ailam<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:8</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'porch'</char></note><verse eid="1KI 7:8"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:9"/>(20) and a beam on both the pillars, and on top of the sides the beam was as a cover in thickness.<verse eid="1KI 7:9"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:10"/>(23) And he made the sea, ten in cubits from its rim to its rim; the same was round in a circle; its height was five in cubits, and drawn together<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:10</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'drawn together':  I.e. 'in total'</char></note>, thirty-three in cubits encompassed it.<verse eid="1KI 7:10"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:11"/>(24) And supports under its rim all round were encircling it, ten in cubits all round, to raise up the sea.<verse eid="1KI 7:11"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:12"/>(26) And its rim was like the work of the rim of a cup, like a bud of a lily, and the thickness of it a handbreadth.<verse eid="1KI 7:12"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:13"/>(25) And twelve oxen were under the sea, the three facing north and the three facing seaward<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:13</char><char closed="false" style="ft">I.e. 'west'</char></note> and the three facing south and the three facing east, and all the hindquarters were toward the house, and the sea was upon them from above.<verse eid="1KI 7:13"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:14"/>(27) And he made ten bronze mechonoth<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:14</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'stand(s) '</char></note>, five cubits the length of the one mechonothd, and four cubits its width and six in cubits its height.<verse eid="1KI 7:14"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:15"/>(28) And this was the work of the mechonothd; they had a stopper, and a stopper between the projections.<verse eid="1KI 7:15"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:16"/>(29) And on their stoppers between the projections were lions and oxen and cheroubin, and on the projections thus: enclosed spaces both above and below the lions and the oxen, a work of descent.<verse eid="1KI 7:16"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:17"/>(30) And the one mechonoth<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:17</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'stand(s) '</char></note> had four bronze wheels and the bronze attachments and their four sides, shoulder<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:17</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Or 'angle'</char></note> pieces under the wash-basins.<verse eid="1KI 7:17"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:18"/>(32) And there were hands<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:18</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Perhaps 'five spokes'</char></note> in the wheels in the mechonoth<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:18</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'stand(s) '</char></note>, and the height of the one wheel was a cubit and a half.<verse eid="1KI 7:18"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:19"/>(33) The work of the wheels was the work of chariot wheels; their hands<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:19</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Perhaps 'five spokes'</char></note> and their backs<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:19</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Perhaps 'rim'</char></note> and their works, the whole castings.<verse eid="1KI 7:19"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:20"/>(34) The four shoulder<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:20</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Or 'angle'</char></note> pieces were at the four corners of the one mechanoth; its shoulders were from the mechanoth<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:20</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'; its shoulders were from the mechanoth':  Hebrew = 'stand(s) '</char></note>.<verse eid="1KI 7:20"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:21"/>(35) And on the top of the mechanothd, half a cubit its size, a circle around on the top of the mechanoth and a beginning of its hands<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:21</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Perhaps 'five spokes'</char></note> and its borders, and it was open at the beginning of its hands<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:21</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Perhaps 'five spokes'</char></note>.<verse eid="1KI 7:21"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:22"/>(36) And its borders were cheroubin and lions and palm trees, standing, each connected on its front, inside and round about.<verse eid="1KI 7:22"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:23"/>(37) Like it<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:23</char><char closed="false" style="ft">I.e. 'the one mechonoth'</char></note>, he made all the ten mechonoth<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:23</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'stand(s) '</char></note>, one order and measure for all.<verse eid="1KI 7:23"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:24"/>(38) And he made ten bronze buckets, the one bucket holding forty chous by measurement; the one bucket on the one mechonoth, for the ten mechonoth<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:24</char><char closed="false" style="ft">', for the ten mechonoth':  Hebrew = 'stand(s) '</char></note>.<verse eid="1KI 7:24"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:25"/>(39) And he placed the ten mechonoth<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:25</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'stand(s) '</char></note>, five on the shoulder<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:25</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Or 'angle'</char></note> of the house on the right and five on the shoulder<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:25</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Or 'angle'</char></note> of the house on the left and the sea on the shoulder<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:25</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Or 'angle'</char></note> of the house on the right, eastward, on the side<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:25</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Perhaps 'slope'</char></note> of the south.<verse eid="1KI 7:25"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:26"/>(40) And Chiram made the cauldrons and the tongs and the saucers, and Chiram finished making all the works that he made for King Salomon in the house of the Lord:<verse eid="1KI 7:26"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:27"/>(41) two pillars and the wreathed works of the pillars on the tops of the two pillars and the two lattice works to cover both the wreathed works of the carvings that were on the pillars,<verse eid="1KI 7:27"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:28"/>(42) the four hundred pomegranates for both the lattice works, two rows of pomegranates for the one latticework, to wrap around both the wreathed works on both the pillars,<verse eid="1KI 7:28"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:29"/>(43) and the ten mechonoth, the ten buckets on the mechonoth<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:29</char><char closed="false" style="ft">', the ten buckets on the mechonoth':  Hebrew = 'stand(s) '</char></note><verse eid="1KI 7:29"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:30"/>(44) and the one sea and the twelve oxen underneath the sea<verse eid="1KI 7:30"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:31"/>(45) and the cauldrons and the tongs and the saucers, all the implements that Chiram made for King Salomon for the house of the Lord, and the forty-eight pillars of the house of the king and the house of the Lord. All the works of the king that Chiram made, entirely of bronze;<verse eid="1KI 7:31"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:32"/>(47) the weight of the bronze of which he made all these works, very much in abundance.<verse eid="1KI 7:32"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:33"/>(46) In the region of the Jordan the king cast them, in the thickness of the ground between Sokchoth and between Sira.<verse eid="1KI 7:33"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:34"/>(48) And King Salomon gave the implements that he made in the house of the Lord: the golden altar, and the table upon which were the loaves of the offering-- golden,<verse eid="1KI 7:34"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:35"/>(49) and the lampstands, five on the right and five on the left, in front of the dabir<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:35</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'inner chamber'</char></note>-- overlaid gold, and the torches and the lamps and the golden pouring vessels<verse eid="1KI 7:35"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:36"/>(50) and the porticoes and the nails and the saucers and the bowls and the golden censers, overlaid, and the doorways of the innermost part of the house, the holy of the holies and the golden doors of the shrine.<verse eid="1KI 7:36"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:37"/>(51) And all the work that King Salomon did on the house of the Lord was fulfilled, and Salomon brought in the holy things of his father Dauid and all the holy things of Salomon, the silver and the gold and the implements, and gave them into the treasuries of the house of the Lord.<verse eid="1KI 7:37"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:38"/>(7.1a) And Salomon built his house in thirteen years.<verse eid="1KI 7:38"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:39"/>(7.2) And he built the House to the Forest of the Lebanon, one hundred cubits its length and fifty cubits its width and thirty cubits its height, and three courses of cedar logs, and cedar shoulders for the logs.<verse eid="1KI 7:39"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:40"/>(7.3) And he paneled the house, from above, on the sides of the logs, and the number of logs was forty-five; the course was fifteen,<verse eid="1KI 7:40"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:41"/>(7.4) and there were three beams and space on space, three times,<verse eid="1KI 7:41"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:42"/>(7.5) and all the doorways and the spaces linked by beams were square and from the doorway on the door three times.<verse eid="1KI 7:42"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:43"/>(7.6) And the Ailam<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:43</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'porch'</char></note> of the Pillars was fifty cubits long and thirty in cubits in width, linked together. There was an ailam in front of them, and pillars and thickness before it<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:43</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Antecedent unclear</char></note> for the ailammin<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:43</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'porches'</char></note>.<verse eid="1KI 7:43"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:44"/>(7.7) And the Ailam<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:44</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'porch'</char></note> of the Thrones, there where he pronounced judgment, Ailam<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:44</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'porch'</char></note> of the Court.<verse eid="1KI 7:44"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:45"/>(7.8) And he had a house, there where he sat, one court evolved for those according to<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:45</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'according to':  Possibly 'engaged in'</char></note> this work, and a house for Pharao's daughter whom Salomon took, corresponding to this ailam<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:45</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'porch'</char></note>.<verse eid="1KI 7:45"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:46"/>(7.9) All these were of costly stones, sculptured at intervals on the inside, even from the foundation to the coping, and on the outside into the great court<verse eid="1KI 7:46"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:47"/>(7.10) founded with large, costly stones, stones of ten cubits and eight cubits.<verse eid="1KI 7:47"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:48"/>(7.11) And above with costly stones, according to the measure of unhewn<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:48</char><char closed="false" style="ft">I.e. 'unhewn stones'</char></note>, and with cedars.<verse eid="1KI 7:48"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:49"/>(7.12) For the great court three courses of unhewn<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">7:49</char><char closed="false" style="ft">I.e. 'unhewn stones'</char></note> and a course of sculptured cedar.<verse eid="1KI 7:49"/>

<verse sid="1KI 7:50"/>(7.1b) And Salomon finished his whole house.<verse eid="1KI 7:50"/>
</_X_chapter>




