<_X_chapter sid="1KI 11">
<verse sid="1KI 11:1"/>And King Salomon was a philogynist. And he had seven hundred ruling women and three hundred concubines. And he took foreign women, both the daughter of Pharao, Moabites, Ammonites, Syrians and Idumeans, Chettites and Amorrites,<verse eid="1KI 11:1"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:2"/>from the nations that the Lord forbade to the sons of Israel: "You shall not go in to them, and they shall not go in to you, lest they turn away your hearts after their idols"; Salomon clung to them for love.<verse eid="1KI 11:2"/>

<verse _X_reasonEmpty="verseEmptyInThisTranslation" sid="1KI 11:3"/><char style="no">&amp;#x2013;</char><note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">11:3</char><char closed="false" style="ft">This verse is empty in this translation.</char></note><verse eid="1KI 11:3"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:4"/>And it happened at the time of Salomon's old age that his heart was not perfect with the Lord, his God, as was the heart of his father Dauid, and his foreign wives turned away his heart after their gods.<verse eid="1KI 11:4"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:5"/>Then Salomon built a high place to Chamos, idol of Moab, and to their king, idol of the sons of Ammon,<verse eid="1KI 11:5"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:6"/>and to Astarte, abomination of the Sidonians.<verse eid="1KI 11:6"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:7"/>And thus he did for all his foreign wives; they were offering incense and sacrificing to their idols,<verse eid="1KI 11:7"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:8"/>and Salomon did evil before the Lord; he did not go after the Lord as Dauid his father.<verse eid="1KI 11:8"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:9"/>And the Lord was angry with Salomon, because his heart had turned away from the Lord God of Israel, who appeared to him twice,<verse eid="1KI 11:9"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:10"/>and commanded him concerning this matter that he should definitely not go after other gods and should keep to do what the Lord God commanded him.<verse eid="1KI 11:10"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:11"/>And the Lord said to Salomon, "Since these things were with you and you did not keep my commandments and my ordinances that I commanded you, tearing I will tear your kingdom from your hand and give it to your slave.<verse eid="1KI 11:11"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:12"/>Yet, for the sake of your father Dauid I will not do them in your days; I will take it out of the hand of your son.<verse eid="1KI 11:12"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:13"/>Yet, I will not take the entire kingdom; I will give one scepter to your son for the sake of my slave Dauid and for the sake of Ierousalem, the city which I chose."<verse eid="1KI 11:13"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:14"/>And the Lord raised up a satan<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">11:14</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'adversary'</char></note> against Salomon, Hader the Idumean (11.23) and Hesrom son of Eliadae who was in Raemmath, Hadrazar, king of Souba, his master, (11.24) and men were gathered around him, and he was leader of a band, and he first captured Damasek, (11.25) and they were a satan<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">11:14</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = 'adversary'</char></note> to Israel all the days of Salomon. And Hader the Idumean was of the seed of the kingdom in Idumea.<verse eid="1KI 11:14"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:15"/>And it happened, when Dauid utterly destroyed Edom while Ioab, commander of the army, went to bury the casualties, that they cut off every male in Idumea<verse eid="1KI 11:15"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:16"/>(for Ioab and all Israel encamped there in Idumea six months until he had eliminated every male from Idumea) ,<verse eid="1KI 11:16"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:17"/>and Hader fled, he and all the Idumean men of the servants of his father with him, and they went into Egypt, and Hader was a young lad.<verse eid="1KI 11:17"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:18"/>And men from the city of Madiam rose up and came into Pharan, and they took men with them and came to Pharao, king of Egypt, and Hader entered in before Pharao, and he gave him a house and arranged food for him.<verse eid="1KI 11:18"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:19"/>And Hader found great favor in the sight of Pharao, and he gave him for a wife a sister of his wife, the elder sister of Thekemina.<verse eid="1KI 11:19"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:20"/>And the sister of Thekemina bore to him-- to Hader-- her son Ganebath, and Thekemina raised him among the sons of Pharao, and Ganebath was among the sons of Pharao.<verse eid="1KI 11:20"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:21"/>And Hader heard in Egypt that Dauid slept with his fathers and that Ioab, the commander of the army, had died, and Hader said to Pharao, "Send me off, and I will return to my land."<verse eid="1KI 11:21"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:22"/>And Pharao said to Hader, "What do you lack with me? And behold, you seek to go to your land." And Hader said to him, "Sending off send me off." And Hader returned to his land.<verse eid="1KI 11:22"/>

<verse _X_reasonEmpty="verseEmptyInThisTranslation" sid="1KI 11:23"/>&amp;#x2013;<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">11:23</char><char closed="false" style="ft">This verse is empty in this translation.</char></note><verse eid="1KI 11:23"/>

<verse _X_reasonEmpty="verseEmptyInThisTranslation" sid="1KI 11:24"/><char style="no">&amp;#x2013;</char><note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">11:24</char><char closed="false" style="ft">This verse is empty in this translation.</char></note><verse eid="1KI 11:24"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:25"/>This was the evil which Hader did, and he was indignant with Israel, and he reigned in the land of Edom.<verse eid="1KI 11:25"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:26"/>And Ieroboam son of Nabat the Ephrathi from Sarira, son of a widow woman, was a slave of Salomon.<verse eid="1KI 11:26"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:27"/>And this was the matter when he lifted up hands against King Salomon. He built the citadel, closed up the fence of the city of David his father,<verse eid="1KI 11:27"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:28"/>and the person Ieroboam was mighty in power, and Salomon saw the lad, that he was a man of action, and he gave him charge over the levies of the house of Ioseph.<verse eid="1KI 11:28"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:29"/>And it happened at that time that Ieroboam went out of Ierousalem, and the prophet Achias the Selonite found him on the way and took him aside out of the way, and Achias had clothed himself with a new garment, and both were in the plain.<verse eid="1KI 11:29"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:30"/>And Achia laid hold of his new garment that was upon him and tore it into twelve pieces.<verse eid="1KI 11:30"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:31"/>And he said to Ieroboam: Take for yourself ten pieces, for this is what the Lord, God of Israel, says, "Behold, I am about to tear the kingdom from the hand of Salomon, and I will give you ten scepters,<verse eid="1KI 11:31"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:32"/>and two scepters will remain his for the sake of my slave Dauid and for the sake of Ierousalem, the city that I chose in it, out of all the tribes of Israel,<verse eid="1KI 11:32"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:33"/>because he forsook me and acted for Astarte, abomination of the Sidonians, and for Chamos and for the idols of Moab and for their king, offense of the sons of Ammon, and he did not go in my ways, to do what is right before me, like his father Dauid.<verse eid="1KI 11:33"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:34"/>And I will certainly not take the whole kingdom out of his hand because, resisting I will resist him all the days of his life, for the sake of my slave Dauid, him whom I chose.<verse eid="1KI 11:34"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:35"/>And I will take the kingdom out of the hand of his son and give you the ten scepters,<verse eid="1KI 11:35"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:36"/>but to his son I will give the two scepters in order that there be an institution for my slave Dauid all the days before me in Ierousalem, the city which I chose for myself to put my name there.<verse eid="1KI 11:36"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:37"/>And I will take you, and you shall reign in what your soul desires, and you shall be king over Israel.<verse eid="1KI 11:37"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:38"/>And it will be, if you keep all that I command you and go in my ways and do what is right before me, to keep my commandments and my ordinances, as Dauid, my slave, did, then I will be with you and will build you a sure house, as I built for Dauid."<verse eid="1KI 11:38"/>

<verse _X_reasonEmpty="verseEmptyInThisTranslation" sid="1KI 11:39"/>&amp;#x2013;<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">11:39</char><char closed="false" style="ft">This verse is empty in this translation.</char></note><verse eid="1KI 11:39"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:40"/>And Salomon sought to put Ieroboam to death, and he arose and fled to Egypt to King Sousakim of Egypt, and he was in Egypt until Salomon died.<verse eid="1KI 11:40"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:41"/>And the rest of the words of Salomon and all that he did and all his discernment, behold, have these not been written in a book of the words of Salomon?<verse eid="1KI 11:41"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:42"/>And the days that Salomon reigned in Ierousalem were forty years.<verse eid="1KI 11:42"/>

<verse sid="1KI 11:43"/>And Salomon slept with his fathers, and they buried him in the city of his father Dauid. And it happened, (12.2) when Ieroboam son of Nabat heard (and he was still in Egypt, since he fled from before Salomon and settled in Egypt) , he went straight and came to his city in the land of Sarira which is in the hill country of Ephraim. And King Salomon slept with his fathers, (11.43) and his son Roboam ruled in his stead.<verse eid="1KI 11:43"/>
</_X_chapter>




