<verse sid="1KI 18:1"/>And it happened after many days that a word of the Lord came to Eliou in the third year, saying, "Go, and appear to Achaab, and I will give rain on the surface of the earth."<verse eid="1KI 18:1"/>

<verse sid="1KI 18:2"/>And Eliou went to appear to Achaab. And the famine was severe in Samaria.<verse eid="1KI 18:2"/>

<verse sid="1KI 18:3"/>And Achaab summoned Abdiou the steward. (And Abdiou was one who revered the Lord greatly,<verse eid="1KI 18:3"/>

<verse sid="1KI 18:4"/>and it happened, when Iezabel smote the prophets of the Lord, that Abdiou took a hundred men, prophets, and hid them by fifty to a cave and kept providing them with bread and water.)<verse eid="1KI 18:4"/>

<verse sid="1KI 18:5"/>And Achaab said to Abdiou, "Come, and let us pass through the land to springs of water and to wadis, if perhaps we may find grass and keep the horses and mules alive, and none of the animals will be destroyed."<verse eid="1KI 18:5"/>

<verse sid="1KI 18:6"/>And they divided for themselves the way to pass through it; Achaab went in one direction alone, and Abdiou went in another direction alone.<verse eid="1KI 18:6"/>

<verse sid="1KI 18:7"/>And Abdiou was on the way alone, and Eliou came to meet him alone, and Abdiou hastened and fell on his face and said, "Are you he, my lord Eliou?"<verse eid="1KI 18:7"/>

<verse sid="1KI 18:8"/>And Eliou said to him, "It is I; go, say to your lord, Behold, Eliou."<verse eid="1KI 18:8"/>

<verse sid="1KI 18:9"/>And Abdiou said, "What have I sinned, that you give your slave into the hand of Achaab, to put me to death?<verse eid="1KI 18:9"/>

<verse sid="1KI 18:10"/>The Lord your God lives, if there is a nation or kingdom to which my lord has not sent to seek you, and they said, 'He is not here,' and he set fire to the kingdom and its regions, because it had not found you.<verse eid="1KI 18:10"/>

<verse sid="1KI 18:11"/>And now you say, 'Go, tell your lord, Behold, Eliou.'<verse eid="1KI 18:11"/>

<verse sid="1KI 18:12"/>And it will be if I depart from you, that a spirit of the Lord will carry you into a land that I know not, and I will go in to tell Achaab, and he will kill me, and your slave is one who reveres the Lord from his youth.<verse eid="1KI 18:12"/>

<verse sid="1KI 18:13"/>Has it not been told to you my lord what I have done when Iezabel killed the prophets of the Lord, that I hid some of the Lord's prophets, a hundred men, by fifty to a cave, and provided them with loaves and water?<verse eid="1KI 18:13"/>

<verse sid="1KI 18:14"/>And now you say to me, 'Go, say to your lord, Behold Eliou,' and he will kill me."<verse eid="1KI 18:14"/>

