<verse sid="1KI 18:24"/>And shout in the name of your gods, and I will call on the name of the Lord, my God, and it will be, the god who answers by fire, he is God." And all the people answered and said, "The word which you spoke is good!"<verse eid="1KI 18:24"/>

<verse sid="1KI 18:25"/>And Eliou said to the prophets of shame, "Choose for yourselves the one bull calf, and do it first, for you are many, and call on the name of your god, and put on no fire."<verse eid="1KI 18:25"/>

<verse sid="1KI 18:26"/>And they took the bull calf and did it and were calling on the name of Baal from morning until noon and said, "Hear us, O Baal, hear us!" And there was no voice, and there was no hearing, and they ran about on the altar that they made.<verse eid="1KI 18:26"/>

<verse sid="1KI 18:27"/>And it happened at noon that Eliou the Thesbite mocked them and said, "Call in a loud voice! For he is a god, for prating<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">18:27</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Possibly 'meditation'</char></note> occupies him, and at the same time he is perhaps giving an oracle, or perhaps he is asleep and will get up."<verse eid="1KI 18:27"/>

