<verse sid="1KI 18:43"/>And he said to his lad, "Go up, and look the way of the sea." And the lad looked and said, "There is nothing." And Eliou said, "Now you-- go again seven times." And the lad returned seven times.<verse eid="1KI 18:43"/>

<verse sid="1KI 18:44"/>And it happened at the seventh time, and behold, a little cloud-- like the sole of a person's foot-- bringing water. And he said, "Go up, and say to Achaab, 'Harness your chariot, and go down; do not let the rain overtake you.' "<verse eid="1KI 18:44"/>

<verse sid="1KI 18:45"/>And it happened until thus and thus<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">18:45</char><char closed="false" style="ft">'until thus and thus':  Perhaps 'after a while'</char></note>, and the sky grew black with clouds and wind, and there was a heavy rain, and Achaab wept and went to Iezrael.<verse eid="1KI 18:45"/>

<verse sid="1KI 18:46"/>And the hand of the Lord was on Eliou, and he girded up his loins and ran in front of Achaab to Iezrael.<verse eid="1KI 18:46"/>
