<verse sid="1KI 20:11"/>And the men of his city, the elders and the freemen who lived in his city, did as Iezabel sent to them, just as it was written in the documents that she sent to them.<verse eid="1KI 20:11"/>

<verse sid="1KI 20:12"/>They called a fast and seated Nabouthai at the head of the people,<verse eid="1KI 20:12"/>

<verse sid="1KI 20:13"/>and two men, sons of transgressors, came and sat opposite him and testified against him, saying, "You have blessed<note caller="▼" style="f"><char closed="false" style="fr">20:13</char><char closed="false" style="ft">Hebrew = euphemism</char></note> God and king," and they took him outside the city and stoned him with stones, and he died.<verse eid="1KI 20:13"/>

<verse sid="1KI 20:14"/>And they sent to Iezabel, saying, "Nabouthai has been stoned and is dead."<verse eid="1KI 20:14"/>

